    "description": "A program that focuses on the systematic study of the spatial distribution and interrelationships of people, natural resources, plant and animal life.  Includes instruction in historical and political geography, cultural geography, economic and physical geography, regional science, cartographic methods, remote sensing, spatial analysis, and applications to areas such as land-use planning, development studies, and analyses of specific countries, regions, and resources.",
