    "title": "Landscape Architecture",
    "description": "A program that prepares individuals for the independent professional practice of landscape architecture and research in various aspects of the field.  Includes instruction in geology and hydrology; soils, groundcovers, and horticultural elements; project and site planning; landscape design, history, and theory; environmental design; applicable law and regulations; and professional responsibilities and standards.",
