    "id": "b25a3547-35a3-440a-a79c-a489209cd432",
    "title": "For Parents/Guardians: Opt Out of Student Search Service™ ",
    "description": " <div>\r\n            <div>\r\n<p>If you no longer want to hear from colleges and scholarship programs that may be a good match for your teen, you can opt out using the form below at any time.  \r\n</p>\r\n<p><b>Is your teen still in the process of choosing a college?</b></br> \r\nRemoving yourself means that your parent contact information will no longer be part of your student’s record and colleges will stop contacting you through Student Search Service. We recommend that you opt out only when your teen has made up their mind, chosen a college, and been accepted. If you have multiple students in the program, please note that submitting this form will remove your information from all of your students’ records.  \r\n</p>\r\n<p><b>Getting too much information from just a few colleges that your teen is no longer interested in?</b></br> \r\nWe recommend that you opt out directly from the communications you receive from those specific colleges. You can typically opt out at the bottom of every email the colleges send you and on their websites. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSubmit this form to be removed from Student Search Service™. \r\n</p>\r\n</br>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div>\r\n                <label for=\"optoutEmail\">Email Address:</label>\r\n                <input type=\"text\" id=\"optoutEmail\" name=\"optoutEmail\">\r\n                <button id=\"optoutbtn\">Remove Email</button>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div id=\"acktext\"></div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <script>\r\n                 function checkEmail(address) {\r\n                var chkRegexp = /^[a-zA-Z0-9.!#$%&'*+/=?^_`{|}~-]+@[a-zA-Z0-9-]+(?:\\.[a-zA-Z0-9-]+)*$/;\r\n                if (address.match(chkRegexp)) {\r\n                    return true;\r\n                } else {\r\n                    return false;\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n            \r\n            function sendRequest(address) {\r\n                var xhrobj = new XMLHttpRequest(); \r\n xhrobj.open('PUT', 'https://parentoptout.cb-omnichannelmcdi-prod.collegeboard.org/parentoptout/parentoptout', true);\r\n                xhrobj.setRequestHeader('X-Api-Key', 'dkfjhgdfirmsfmcparentoptinxyefgthkhg');\r\n                xhrobj.setRequestHeader(\"Content-type\", \"application/json\");\r\n                myJson = {\"parentemail\" : emailaddress.value};\r\n                console.log(JSON.stringify(myJson));\r\n                xhrobj.send(JSON.stringify(myJson));\r\n  \r\n                xhrobj.onload = () => {\r\n                    if (xhrobj.status == 200) {\r\n                        document.getElementById('acktext').innerHTML = 'Request sent.';\r\n                console.log(JSON.parse(xhrobj.response));\r\n                    } else {                        \r\n                        document.getElementById('acktext').innerHTML = 'Current technical issues try again later.';\r\n                console.error('Error!');\r\n                    }\r\n                };\r\n\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            const btn = document.getElementById('optoutbtn');\r\n            const emailaddress = document.getElementById('optoutEmail');\r\n                    \r\n            btn.addEventListener('click', function handleClick() {\r\n            var email = emailaddress.value;\r\n                       \r\n                if (checkEmail(email)){\r\n                    sendRequest(email);\r\n                } else {\r\n                    btn.textContent = 'Remove Valid Email Address';\r\n                    emailaddress.focus();\r\n                }\r\n                         \r\n            });       \r\n        </script>",
    "readTime": "5 min read",
